   Higher Education Information Center (HEIC)
   http://www.edinfo.org/
   HEIC is a Boston based service of The Education Resources Institute
   (TERI) that promotes college access and awareness for people of all
   ages, especially first generation college students. It provides
   information, counseling and advocacy.
   Related Topics: Preparing for college  Parents  pay for your education
   State financial aid  Diversity
